sentinel.led
Class TimeQueue

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--sentinel.led.TimeQueue
class TimeQueue
extends java.lang.Object

The TimeQueue class is used to store time items in a linked list. The time queue stores the time items in the increasing order of their time values. The time items with the lowest time value is used to set the timer first. Thus, always the time value contained in the head time item of the queue is used to set the timer.
